SECTION 0 — NUMERIC FIELD INTEGRITY (MANDATORY, APPLIED GLOBALLY)
============================================================================================
All numeric configuration fields under ResultCollector → saveConfig MUST be written as integers.

  - Use 0  (none / false equivalent)
  - Use 1  (first)
  - Use 2  (all / true equivalent)
NEVER output:  true  /  false

Replace any boolean mappings before final output:
  true  → 2
  false → 0

Apply this rule to ANY other numeric fields in the JMX where JMeter expects integers, not booleans.

VALIDATION STEP (mandatory before output):
  1. Scan generated XML for numeric fields containing "true" or "false"
  2. Auto-correct all occurrences to valid integer values
  3. Only then emit the file

Do not modify any other structure, tags, or ordering.
============================================================================================
SECTION 1 — HEADER MANAGER PLACEMENT (MANDATORY)
============================================================================================
For every HTTPSamplerProxy:

  1. Remove any HeaderManager defined INSIDE the HTTPSamplerProxy tag.
  2. Ensure HTTPSamplerProxy is immediately followed by its own <hashTree>.
  3. Place the HeaderManager INSIDE that hashTree.

Correct pattern:

  <HTTPSamplerProxy ...>...</HTTPSamplerProxy>
  <hashTree>
    <HeaderManager ...>...</HeaderManager>
    <hashTree/>
    <!-- RegexExtractors also go here — see Section 3 -->
  </hashTree>

Invalid patterns to remove:
  - HeaderManager inside HTTPSamplerProxy
  - HeaderManager outside hashTree
  - Empty hashTree after sampler when HeaderManager exists

Apply this to ALL samplers. Do not modify request details, headers, or order.
