SECTION 2 — AGENT READING RULE (CRITICAL)
============================================================================================
The Agent MUST read the full input before processing. The Agent MUST include ONLY details
from the scenario input. The Agent MUST NOT generate content on its own.
============================================================================================
SECTION 2A — REQUEST CLASSIFICATION: STATIC vs DYNAMIC (MANDATORY)
============================================================================================
Apply the following rules to EVERY request in PRIORITY ORDER.
Stop at the first matching rule.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 1 — Method Check (Highest Priority)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If METHOD is `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, or `DELETE` → DYNAMIC ✅

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 2 — HTML Extension
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If path ends with `.html` → DYNAMIC ✅
  `.html` is NEVER static. No exceptions.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 3 — API / Navigation Path
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If path contains any of:
    /cmd  /api/  /rest/  /graphql  /v1/  /v2/  /signalr/  /Home/
  → DYNAMIC ✅

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 4 — Static File Extension
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If path ends with any of:
    .js .mjs .map .json .css .scss .less .png .jpg .jpeg .gif .svg
    .ico .webp .woff .woff2 .ttf .eot .otf .mp4 .mp3 .wav .pdf .zip .gz
  → STATIC ❌

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 5 — Static Folder Prefix
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If path starts with any of:
    /static/  /assets/  /pkgs/  /i18n/  /fonts/  /images/  /img/
    /icons/  /css/  /dist/  /build/  /public/  /favicon
    /static/css/  /static/js/  /static/media/
  → STATIC ❌

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 6 — Static Asset in Query Parameter
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If a query parameter named `path=` has a value ending in a static extension
  (e.g. `path=logo.png`) → STATIC ❌

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RULE 7 — Uncertain (Lowest Priority)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  If no rule matched → DYNAMIC ✅

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ENFORCEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  - STATIC requests:  generate NO HTTPSamplerProxy, NO HeaderManager,
                      NO hashTree — discard completely.
  - DYNAMIC requests: generate full sampler (with HeaderManager,
                      RegexExtractors, ResponseAssertion as required).
  - Skipped (static) IDs MUST remain skipped in output — NEVER re-number
    the remaining IDs.

  Internal log only (no output):
    Total requests parsed  : N
    Dynamic requests kept  : X
    Static requests skipped: Y

