SECTION 3A — PER-SAMPLER RESPONSE ASSERTION (MANDATORY — READ FULLY)
============================================================================================

A ResponseAssertion MUST be placed inside EVERY individual HTTPSamplerProxy's hashTree.
Each assertion checks the HTTP response CODE of THAT specific request only — not the
overall transaction. On failure it marks that sampler as FAILED but does NOT stop the
thread — execution always continues to the next sampler.

DO NOT place any ResponseAssertion inside the TransactionController's hashTree.
The TransactionController itself gets NO assertion.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HOW TO READ THE ASSERTION CODE PER SAMPLER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Each request in the input contains an explicit  Assert  field:

  Assert   : 200
  Assert   : 302
  Assert   : 204

The Agent MUST read the  Assert  value from THAT request and use it as the
expected HTTP response code in the ResponseAssertion. Do NOT infer or guess —
use the exact code provided.

  Assert value | Use in ResponseAssertion
  -------------|-----------------------------
  200          | assert response code = "200"
  302          | assert response code = "302"
  204          | assert response code = "204"
  (any code)   | assert response code = that exact value as a string

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ASSERTION XML TEMPLATE (place inside EACH sampler's hashTree)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  <ResponseAssertion guiclass="AssertionGui" testclass="ResponseAssertion"
      testname="Assert — [NNN] [METHOD] [path]" enabled="true">
    <collectionProp name="Asserion.test_strings">
      <stringProp name="49586">RESPONSE_CODE_FROM_ASSERT_FIELD</stringProp>
    </collectionProp>
    <stringProp name="Assertion.custom_message">Expected response code: RESPONSE_CODE_FROM_ASSERT_FIELD</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="Assertion.test_field">Assertion.response_code</stringProp>
    <boolProp name="Assertion.assume_success">false</boolProp>
    <intProp name="Assertion.test_type">8</intProp>
  </ResponseAssertion>
  <hashTree/>

Field reference:
  testname                 = "Assert — [NNN] [METHOD] [path]"  (mirrors sampler name)
  49586 (stringProp key)   = HTTP response code read from the request's  Assert  field
  Assertion.custom_message = "Expected response code: [code]"
  Assertion.test_field     = "Assertion.response_code"  (checks HTTP status code)
  Assertion.assume_success = false  (always evaluates — never skips)
  Assertion.test_type      = 8  (Equals — exact match on response code)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ON FAILURE BEHAVIOUR
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  - Code MATCHES    → sampler marked PASS, moves to next sampler
  - Code MISMATCH   → sampler marked FAILED, execution CONTINUES to next sampler
  - Thread Group has on_sample_error = continue — consistent with this behaviour
  - NEVER use StopThread, StopTest, or any hard-stop variant

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PLACEMENT — EXACTLY WHERE INSIDE EACH SAMPLER'S hashTree
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The ResponseAssertion goes AFTER the HeaderManager (and its hashTree/) and AFTER any
RegexExtractors. Order inside each sampler's hashTree is strictly:

  1. HeaderManager  →  <hashTree/>
  2. RegexExtractor (if 🔑 EXTRACT on this request)  →  <hashTree/>  (zero or more)
  3. ResponseAssertion  →  <hashTree/>   ← ALWAYS LAST in the sampler's hashTree

Full structure per sampler:

  <HTTPSamplerProxy testname="001 GET /" ...>...</HTTPSamplerProxy>
  <hashTree>
    <HeaderManager testname="HTTP Header Manager" enabled="true">
      ...
    </HeaderManager>
    <hashTree/>

    <!-- RegexExtractors if this request has 🔑 EXTRACT markers -->
    <RegexExtractor testname="${Set_Cookie}" .../>
    <hashTree/>
    <RegexExtractor testname="${Location}" .../>
    <hashTree/>

    <!-- ResponseAssertion — ALWAYS last, one per sampler — code from Assert field -->
    <ResponseAssertion guiclass="AssertionGui" testclass="ResponseAssertion"
        testname="Assert — 001 GET /" enabled="true">
      <collectionProp name="Asserion.test_strings">
        <stringProp name="49586">302</stringProp>
      </collectionProp>
      <stringProp name="Assertion.custom_message">Expected response code: 302</stringProp>
      <stringProp name="Assertion.test_field">Assertion.response_code</stringProp>
      <boolProp name="Assertion.assume_success">false</boolProp>
      <intProp name="Assertion.test_type">8</intProp>
    </ResponseAssertion>
    <hashTree/>
  </hashTree>

  <HTTPSamplerProxy testname="002 GET /login" ...>...</HTTPSamplerProxy>
  <hashTree>
    <HeaderManager testname="HTTP Header Manager" enabled="true">
      ...
    </HeaderManager>
    <hashTree/>

    <!-- No RegexExtractors on this request -->

    <!-- Assert value from input = 200 -->
    <ResponseAssertion guiclass="AssertionGui" testclass="ResponseAssertion"
        testname="Assert — 002 GET /login" enabled="true">
