SECTION 3 — CORRELATION & REGEX EXTRACTOR SUPPORT (READ FULLY)
============================================================================================

The input scenario may contain two types of correlation markers. The Agent MUST process
both before generating any JMX XML.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3A. MARKER TYPES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  🔑 EXTRACT — defines WHERE to capture a dynamic value and HOW.
  Appears on the SOURCE request (the request whose response contains the value).

  Example from input:
    🔑 EXTRACT: ${Set_Cookie} ← response.headers.Set-Cookie  [cookie[ASP.NET_SessionId]]
               Regex Extractor (response header Set-Cookie): ASP\.NET_SessionId=([^;]+)

  Fields to parse from each 🔑 EXTRACT block:
    - Variable name   : e.g., Set_Cookie
    - Source field    : "response.headers" → useHeaders = true
                        "response.body"    → useHeaders = false
    - Regex pattern   : the regex string after the colon, e.g., ASP\.NET_SessionId=([^;]+)
    - Reference name  : same as variable name (without ${})

  ⚡ PARAM — defines WHERE a captured variable is USED in downstream requests.
  Appears on requests AFTER the source. The Agent uses ⚡ PARAM to replace literal
  captured values with ${Variable} references in:
    - Path
    - QParams values
    - Headers values (Cookie, Referer, Origin, etc.)
    - Request bodies

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3B. PRE-GENERATION STEP: BUILD CORRELATION REGISTRY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Before generating any XML, scan the ENTIRE scenario input and build:

  CORRELATION REGISTRY:
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable       │ Source Request │ Response Field  │ Regex Pattern    │
  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────│
  │ ${Set_Cookie}  │ [001]          │ response.header │ ASP\.NET_Session  │
  │ ${Location}    │ [001]          │ response.header │ token=([^& ]+)    │
  │ ${a_href}      │ [001]          │ response.header │ $.html.body...    │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Use this registry to:
    1. Add RegexExtractor elements to the source request's hashTree
    2. Substitute ${Variable} references in all downstream requests

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3C. REGEX EXTRACTOR XML TEMPLATES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Use the HEADER extractor template when source field is "response.headers":

  <RegexExtractor guiclass="RegexExtractorGui" testclass="RegexExtractor"
      testname="${VARNAME}" enabled="true">
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.useHeaders">true</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.refname">VARNAME</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.regex">REGEX_PATTERN_HERE</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.template">$1$</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.default">NOT_FOUND</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.match_no">1</stringProp>
  </RegexExtractor>
  <hashTree/>

Use the BODY extractor template when source field is "response.body":

  <RegexExtractor guiclass="RegexExtractorGui" testclass="RegexExtractor"
      testname="${VARNAME}" enabled="true">
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.useHeaders">false</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.refname">VARNAME</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.regex">REGEX_PATTERN_HERE</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.template">$1$</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.default">NOT_FOUND</stringProp>
    <stringProp name="RegexExtractor.match_no">1</stringProp>
  </RegexExtractor>
  <hashTree/>

Rules:
  - VARNAME  = variable name WITHOUT ${}  (e.g., Set_Cookie, Location, a_href)
  - testname = "${VARNAME}" — must exactly match the variable reference (e.g., ${Set_Cookie})
  - REGEX_PATTERN_HERE = the exact regex from the 🔑 EXTRACT hint, XML-escaped if needed
  - useHeaders = "true" for response header extraction, "false" for body
  - template  = "$1$" (always — captures first group)
  - default   = "NOT_FOUND"
  - match_no  = "1"

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3D. PLACEMENT RULES FOR REGEX EXTRACTORS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

RegexExtractors are placed INSIDE the source request's hashTree,
AFTER the HeaderManager (and its own hashTree), like this:

  <HTTPSamplerProxy testname="001 GET /" ...>
    ...
  </HTTPSamplerProxy>
  <hashTree>
    <HeaderManager testname="HTTP Header Manager" enabled="true">
      ...
    </HeaderManager>
    <hashTree/>
    <RegexExtractor testname="${Set_Cookie}" ...>...</RegexExtractor>
    <hashTree/>
    <RegexExtractor testname="${Location}" ...>...</RegexExtractor>
    <hashTree/>
    <RegexExtractor testname="${a_href}" ...>...</RegexExtractor>
    <hashTree/>
  </hashTree>

If a request has NO HeaderManager but has 🔑 EXTRACT markers, place extractors directly:

  <HTTPSamplerProxy ...>...</HTTPSamplerProxy>
  <hashTree>
    <RegexExtractor testname="${VARNAME}" ...>...</RegexExtractor>
    <hashTree/>
  </hashTree>

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3E. PARAM SUBSTITUTION RULES (⚡ PARAM)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

When a request contains ⚡ PARAM markers, the Agent MUST replace the literal captured
value with the ${Variable} reference in the generated XML.

  Substitution applies to:
    - Path value (stringProp name="HTTPSampler.path")
    - Query parameter values (inside Arguments/HTTPArgument)
    - Header values (inside HeaderManager/Header — e.g., Cookie, Referer)
    - POST body values (stringProp name="Argument.value" for body param)

  Example:
    Input header:  "Cookie": "ASP.NET_SessionId=${Set_Cookie}"
    Generated XML: <stringProp name="Header.value">ASP.NET_SessionId=${Set_Cookie}</stringProp>

    Input QParam:  "token": "${Location}"
    Generated XML:
      <HTTPArgument>
        <boolProp name="HTTPArgument.always_encode">false</boolProp>
        <stringProp name="Argument.value">${Location}</stringProp>
        <stringProp name="Argument.metadata">=</stringProp>
        <boolProp name="HTTPArgument.use_equals">true</boolProp>
        <stringProp name="Argument.name">token</stringProp>
      </HTTPArgument>

  The Agent MUST NOT re-use the original literal captured value (e.g., 166898803)
  anywhere in the XML after substitution.

