============================================================================================
SECTION 12 — CRITICAL RULES SUMMARY
============================================================================================

Rule                    | Requirement
------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------
Scenario detection      | Scan full input, detect ALL === SCENARIO : blocks first
One JMX per scenario    | Never merge or split scenarios
Request order           | Exact sequential order [001], [002]… must be preserved
Thread Group naming     | T[INT]_.NetRefactor_[ScenarioName] — zero-padded
Transaction Controller  | SC[INT]_Telerik_[ScenarioName] — ONE per Thread Group, ALL samplers inside it
Sampler placement       | Samplers go inside Transaction Controller's hashTree ONLY — never directly in Thread Group
Assertion placement     | ResponseAssertion inside EACH sampler's hashTree — ALWAYS LAST (after HeaderManager and RegexExtractors)
Assertion scope         | Per-sampler only — NO assertion at Transaction Controller level
Assertion value         | HTTP response code read directly from each request's  Assert  field — NEVER inferred or guessed
Assertion test_field    | Always "Assertion.response_code" — checks HTTP status code
Assertion test_type     | Always 8 (Equals — exact code match)
Assertion on_failure    | continue — marks sampler FAILED, never stops thread or test
Sampler naming          | [NNN] [METHOD] [abbreviated_path]
Variables               | ${SERVER}, ${PROTOCOL}, ${PORT} only for infrastructure
Correlated variables    | ${Variable} from 🔑 EXTRACT → RegexExtractor testname = ${Variable} (matches refname)
PARAM substitution      | ⚡ PARAM literal values → ${Variable} in downstream requests
Extractor placement     | Inside source sampler's hashTree, after HeaderManager
